15 FUTURE WITHOUT THE NEED FOR COURT INTERVENTION;
16 (15) THE CHILD’S PREFERENCE, IF AGE–APPROPRIATE; AND
17 (16) ANY OTHER FACTOR THAT THE COURT CONSIDERS APPROPRIATE
18 IN DETERMINING HOW BEST TO SERVE THE PHYSICAL, DEVELOPMENTAL, AND
19 EMOTIONAL NEEDS OF THE CHILD.
20 (B) THE COURT SHALL ARTICULATE ITS FINDINGS OF FACT ON THE RECORD
21 OR IN A WRITTEN OPINION, INCLUDING THE CONSIDERATION OF EACH FACTOR
22 LISTED IN SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION AND ANY OTHER FACTOR THAT THE
23 COURT CONSIDERED.
